        <prompt>How did the "crop-lien" system affect Southern agriculture?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Created a cycle of debt for farmers</option>
            <option letter="b">Improved agricultural productivity</option>
            <option letter="c">Increased farmer independence</option>
            <option letter="d">Reduced cotton production</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The crop-lien system created a cycle of debt for farmers who had to mortgage their future crops for current supplies at high interest rates.</explanation>
